# Canonical design-contract files are checksum-governed (see
# frontend/frontend-coding-contract/canonical-manifest.sha256). Any
# line-ending normalization on checkout/stash/merge silently changes their
# bytes and breaks the checksum without touching their visible content -- this
# has happened by accident before. Keep them exactly as committed regardless
# of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
frontend/frontend-coding-contract/design-pages/* -text
